args: Milady! Oh, I can't tell you how afraid I\nwas that I might never see you again!\nWAAAAAAH!
Sorry to make you worry, Chitose. The\ntrip was worth it, thoughâ€”we found out\nthe truth behind all the disappearances.
And with THAT, the investigation's all\ndone and wrapped nice with a bow.\nIsn't that swell?
The LAST thing we want to do is incur\nAmaterasu's wrath by butting in on her\nbusiness, guys.

(She speaks true. Had we forced that
couple to return, it could have been
interpreted as us presuming ourselves
above an act of divinity...)
(Nonetheless, I cannot turn a blind eye!)
I am going to continue the investigation\non my own, Mitsuhide.
Uhhh, I JUST said we shouldn't poke our\nnoses where they don't belong.
I know that, but I remain...unconvinced.\nIs that couple TRULY happy?
Is there not a way for them to live\nhappily here? In this world? I cannot\nrest until I discover this for myself!
Far be it from me to stop you, Nobunaga.\nBut as the leader of the Mouse Clan,\nI'll have no part of this.
We're out of here, Daikokutenâ€”BEFORE\nwe end up bringing the wrath of the\nheavens down on our heads, preferably.
Er, Lady Mitsuhide, did I miss something?
Better for you not to get involved, Chitose.\nThere is a reason why Mitsuhide has\nelected to leave matters as they are.
Look, I may be overstepping by nosing in\non what seems like a big ol' secret, but...
I can't bear the thought of my loved ones\ndisappearing before my eyesâ€”especially\nwithout being given a chance to stop it!

To disobey Lady Mitsuhide's orders would
be to disgrace myself as her attendant...
But as her protector, I want to know the
truth behind what's been going on.
Lady Nobunaga, please! Tell me what's\ngoing on. I want to help, whatever it is!
Very well, Chitose. I acknowledge your\nconviction! Now, listen well!
Whaaat?! Amaterasu is responsible for\nthe disappearances?! That's wild!
The merchant couple accepted her\ninvitation to a life of peace, and thus\nwere sent to that other realm.
But that ï¼‚peaceï¼‚ is false! I refuse to\nbelieve that Amaterasu would so callously\nerase people from this world!
How is that any different from straight-up\nkidnapping them? We need to get to the\nbottom of this, Lady Nobunaga!
And so, under Nobunaga's direction,\nChitose began to investigate.\nAfter several days...
Lady Nobunaga! Come here!\nYou have to see this!

Oho! This document is unmistakable
proof that they had an attachment to
this world! They wanted to open their
own restaurant.

They labored towards this goal day after
day, saving bit by bit. They had even
chosen a location, and were on the
cusp of opening shop.
But in the end, they didn't. Why did they\ngive up on their dreams, I wonder?
Who knows? They must have had their\nreasons. We have but to ask them directly.
I do. We will once again abscond to that\nother realm, and I have already secured\nthe means!
So this is where you all were whisked\noff to?
Indeed. Daikokuten bit into this pillar,\nand we were spirited away. And by that\ntokenâ€”
Something came out of the pillar!\nWhoa, wait a sec! This is a gleamshard!
As I suspected. But wait...\nNo, this cannot be!
I sliced only the pillar. Why in the world\nwould the gleamshard be damaged?
Sooorry! I am quite sure that's my fault.
When I bit the pillar, I also nipped the\ngleamshard! Whoops!
Mitsuhide asked me to deliver this to you!
It was given to her by Amaterasu to use\nin her new year's journey. And now it's\nyours!
But why? I thought Mitsuhide had washed\nher hands of this matter.
As the leader of the Mouse Clan, yes!\nBut is she not also your dear friend?
Hah. Rather roundabout, but also\nvery much in character for her.
I'm in your debt. I will gladly use this\ngleamshard! Chitose, Daikokutenâ€”\nget back!
You can't mean to go in alone!
If we want to rescue that couple, discretion\nis essential. Going alone will permit me to\nresolve this without too much provocation.
...I see. Very well! Come back safe!
I must impose upon you once more,\ncitizens!
Ack! Wh-what's going on?!\nYou have returned?!
Indeed! I will return as many times as\nnecessary, if it means guiding you to\nhappiness!
I thought we had explained that our\nhappiness is living here in tranquility...
Do you truly mean that?! Did you not\nonce have dreams in the real world?!
What?! H-how do you know that?!
I conducted an investigation. I know of\nyour plans to open a restaurant.
Why did you give up when you were on the\ncusp of realizing your ambitions?
...We didn't give up. If we COULD open\nit, we would. Even now.
But that dream is dead. Our home was\nrobbed, depriving us of everything we\nhad saved.
We spent years saving up that money!\nAnd then in a single night...gone!
The miseryâ€”the crueltyâ€”it was too much!\nThat's why we grew tired of living!
...I see. The injustice of the world tore\nyour frail hearts asunder. Your feelings\nare understandable.
Those possessed of virtue but weak of\nconstitution are as a tiny boat, tossed to\nand fro by the tempestuous seas of grief.

Yet that frailty must be protected! It is
the duty of the strong to cut through the
injustice of the world and guide the people
towards happiness! That is their destiny!
Listen to me! I will take responsibility\nfor your dream!
What?! But our dream is alreadyâ€”

I will tread upon every last blade of grass
in Hinomoto to capture this thief! Your
funds will be returned to you if it is the
last thing I do!
You would really do such a thing?!
I shall cut through the impossible to make\nit possible! That is the essence of who I\nam: Nobunaga, of the Twelve Wyrmclans!
Take my hand, and open your eyes!\nWe make for the new beginnings that\nawait you in the real world!
If someone in your position would truly\nstake so much upon helping us...then we\naccept. We will entrust our dreams to you.
Yes. I will believe in youâ€”in your\nstrength, and in your hope.
Your faith is well-placed. Together,\nwe will make your dreams come true!
Oh, welcome back, Lady Nobunaga!\nAnd you two, as well!
Indeed! Consider this matter resolved!\nYet more remains to be done.
We have yet to uncover the truth behind\nthe disappearances. What in the world is\nAmaterasu's true aim?
